    <p class="eyebrow">Help improve the site</p>
    <h1>Contact and corrections</h1>
    <p class="lede">Use the question-reporting tool for item-specific issues and email for broader site concerns.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="page-shell legal-page">
    <div class="contact-options">
      <article class="contact-option">
        <h2>Question correction</h2>
        <p>
          Open the question in a live test or results review and select
          <strong>Report question</strong>. The report automatically includes the
          question ID, session data version, and displayed answer order.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--small" href="/security-plus/sy0-701/practice-test/">Open the Security+ practice test</a>
      </article>

      <article class="contact-option">
        <h2>Technical or general message</h2>
        <p>
          Send a message to <strong>{{ site.contactAddress }}</strong>.
          Include the page address, browser, device type, and a brief description when
          reporting a website problem.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="contact-option">
        <h2>Privacy question</h2>
        <p>
          Send privacy questions to <strong>{{ site.privacyAddress }}</strong>
          for questions about stored reports, browser-session behavior, or the
          <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="contact-option">
        <h2>Vendor or trademark concern</h2>
        <p>
          Send the concern to <strong>{{ site.contactAddress }}</strong>
          and identify the certification, page address, and concern. Cert Happens is
          an independent resource and takes attribution issues seriously.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
